# Astro Starter - Project Rules

## Stack

- Framework: Astro 5+
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Vanilla CSS with CSS custom properties
- Hosting: Cloudflare Pages (static)

## Styling Approach

- Use CSS custom properties defined in `src/styles/global.css`
- Prefer scoped `<style>` blocks in components for component-specific styles
- Use global utility classes from global.css for common patterns
- No CSS-in-JS or Tailwind — keep it vanilla and readable

## CSS Variables

- Colors: `--color-bg`, `--color-text`, `--color-accent`, etc.
- Typography: `--text-sm`, `--text-base`, `--font-serif`, etc.
- Spacing: `--space-1` through `--space-32`
- Use these consistently rather than hardcoding values

## Component Guidelines

- Use `.astro` components for static content (no client JS)
- Only add `<script>` tags when interactivity is truly needed
- For complex interactivity, use React/Vue/Svelte islands sparingly
- Props interface should be defined with TypeScript `interface Props`

## File Structure

```
src/
├── components/    # Reusable Astro components
├── layouts/       # Page layouts (Layout.astro, BaseLayout.astro)
├── pages/         # File-based routing
└── styles/        # Global CSS
```

## Image Handling

- Use Astro's `<Image>` component for local images
- For external images (CMS), use `<img>` with proper width/height
- Always include meaningful alt text

## Performance

- Astro outputs zero JS by default — keep it that way when possible
- Use `loading="lazy"` for below-fold images
- Preload critical fonts in Layout.astro head

